  "text": "The results we summarize here are based on Principle Components Analysis of 129 electrodes followed by analysis of variance of experimental variables on 9 electrodes (the 10-20 system). In the pronunciation decision task, graphic similarity effects were observed at 200 ms after the onset of the second character in the reduction of a positivegoing shift (P200) associated with graphic processing. Source analysis low resolution electromagnetic tomography (LORETA Pascual; [CITATION_1] identified the source of this graphic component at bilateral occipital and prefrontal motor areas, identified also by in an ERP study of Chinese word identification and by [CITATION_2] in an fMRI study.",
